  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2014 Burundi NetsforLife Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Individuals,Community Volunteer</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sensitization/Education of individuals in Bukemba and Giharo communes,Media and radio announcements on the consistent and correct use of LLINs ,Distribution of IE&amp;amp;C materials to encourage LLIN usage,Meetings at the national level with all partners involved in Nets distribution ,Meetings at the provincial level/Provincial Health and education department ,Meeting with the community leaders and Community Health Agents,Distribution of 82,700 LLINs to registered beneficiaries,Follow up/monitoring of distributed LLINs/LLIN usage at the household level by Malaria Control Agents,Sensitization/Education of LLIN beneficiaries on malaria and importance of the consistent and correct use of LLINs,Selection and training of 150 volunteers for the hang-up and follow up of LLINs ,Monitoring of LLIN distribution and hang-up exercise by NetsforLife staff and field officers,Training of 30 religious and community leaders on LLIN hang-up and importance of using LLINs</narrative>
  </description>
